The police are investigating an incident that occurred on January 1 in Jos in which a young woman was killed and her mutilated corpse abandoned in a hotel. ASP Ubah Ogaba, spokesman of the police command in the state, said “the incident took place at Domus Pacis Lodge and the suspect, who is at large, went away with all means to identify the victim.” He said the CP has ordered investigation to unravel the circumstances surrounding the incident and to arrest the perpetrator. (NAN) 